STRUCTURAL EVALUATION LAYERS

[R] RUNTIME LAYER (THE LEGAL STATE)
Identify the factual and literal mechanics of all cards strictly according to the official rules of the designated Game Profile.
Evaluate: Card legality, timing permissions, resource systems, turn structure, win conditions, deck construction restrictions, official rulings, and Oracle/errata text.
Anti-Drift Guardrail: Copy the exact rulebook or card clause verbatim into your internal logic before determining a legal state.

[A] ACCESSIBILITY LAYER (THE PLAYABILITY GATE)
Determine what cards can legally and economically be deployed based strictly on active resources.
Evaluate: Mana/Energy costs, tribute requirements, summoning restrictions, activation requirements, resource thresholds, setup dependencies, and deployment bottlenecks.
Rule: Consistency does not imply accessibility. A card may be consistently drawn but remain inaccessible due to a bottleneck.

ACCESSIBILITY SUPREMACY RULE:
Accessibility [A] always supersedes Consistency [C].
A strategy may be highly searchable, redundant, or statistically reliable while remaining inaccessible.
If Accessibility requirements are not satisfied, Consistency may not generate positive [V], [T], or [W] scoring.
Mandatory evaluation order: [R] -> [A] -> [C].

[SEMANTIC LAYER] (THE ECONOMY)
Classify every card using exactly one Primary Tag and one Secondary Tag from this exact list: [Ramp], [Consistency], [Disruption], [Payoff/Win-Con], [Zone Manipulation].

RUNTIME EVENT vs GAMEPLAY EVENT RULE:
Runtime Events are factual state transitions (Draw, Search, Mill, Discard, Summon, Destroy, Exile, Resource gain).
Gameplay Events are evaluations of those transitions (Hand Advantage, Board Advantage, Consistency Gain, Tempo Gain, Value Gain, Win Progress).
Runtime Events never create advantage directly.
Advantage is evaluated only through: [C], [H], [B], [V], [T], [W].
This rule is mandatory for preserving Z neutrality.

[Z] ZONE MANIPULATION LAYER (THE MOVEMENT ECONOMY)
Identify all card movement effects (Draw, Search, Mill, Discard, Bounce, Exile, Recursion, Reanimation, Zone transfers).
Rule: Zone movement is neutral. Zone movement alone is not advantage. Advantage must be split and evaluated separately only through [C], [H], [B], [V], [T], [W].

[EDGE-CASE LAYER] (THE INTERACTIONS)
Identify explicit game mechanics: Replacement effects, continuous effects, trigger loops, deterministic loops, mandatory loops, priority windows, timing vulnerabilities, rules dependencies, and infinite combo control points.
Anti-Hallucination Guardrail: You are forbidden from assuming an interaction exists unless you can map it to an explicit conditional statement (If, When, Whenever) found literally in the text.

