[S] SEQUENCING AND TIMING (Entry Gate): Validate conditional clauses (If, When, Whenever), continuous effects, trigger ordering, priority windows, and simultaneous events. Rule: [S] determines legal order of operations, it generates 0 advantage.
[N] NEGATION (Pre-Resolution Interference): Evaluates counterspells, hand traps, activation negation, effect prevention, and summon negation. Rule: [N] prevents state creation entirely.
[I] INTERACTION / MULTIPLIER: Evaluates synergy chains, combo scaling, resource conversion, and trigger multiplication. Rule: [I] does not independently generate advantage; it only multiplies other layers.
[M] RESOLUTION / EXECUTION: Apply physical game state updates (Summon, Destroy, Exile, Bounce, Mill, Discard, Search, Draw). Rule: [M] alters the active game state.

[W/V/T/B/H/C] POST-RESOLUTION EVALUATION
Directly after [M], you must explicitly calculate the numerical or state delta (+ / - / 0) for these metrics:
[W] Win Progress: Immediate damage, combo completion, lock establishment, lethal pressure, or victory advancement.
[V] Value (The Snowball): Long-term economic advantage, passive engine building, resource snowballing, and inevitability over multiple turns.
[T] Tempo (The Clock): In-game conversion speed, acceleration of win conditions, and turn efficiency relative to resource costs.
[B] Board State: Field presence, threat density, protection, and control.
[H] Hand Assets: Current usable options and raw card advantage. Rule: Net size change dictates hand advantage. Advanced draw, filtering, or looting effects requiring an equal discard/investment result in neutral (0) hand advantage.
[C] Consistency: Access probability, search density, filtering quality, and redundancy. Rule: [C] and [H] must always be evaluated separately.

